      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Broadcasting rules apply, see the "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.linalg.html",
              "href": "",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "linalg",
              "text": "we.linalg"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " documentation for\ndetails."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The solutions are computed using LAPACK routine "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "_gesv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " must be square and of full-rank, i.e., all rows (or, equivalently,\ncolumns) must be linearly independent; if either is not true, use\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "lstsq"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " for the least-squares best \"solution\" of the\nsystem/equation."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "argument_inline": [],
          "content_blocks": [],
          "directive": "versionchanged",
          "options": [],
          "raw_source": ".. versionchanged:: 2.0\n\n   The b array is only treated as a shape (M,) column vector if it is\n   exactly 1-dimensional. In all other instances it is treated as a stack\n   of (M, K) matrices. Previously b would be treated as a stack of (M,)\n   vectors if b.ndim was equal to a.ndim - 1.",
          "supported": true,
          "type": "directive_block",
          "version": "2.0"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nG. Strang, Linear Algebra and Its Applications, 2nd Ed., Orlando,\nFL, Academic Press, Inc., 1980, pg. 22.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Solve the system of equations:\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x0 + 2 * x1 = 1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "3 * x0 + 5 * x1 = 2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ":"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = we.array([[1, 2], [3, 5]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "b = we.array([1, 2])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = we.linalg.solve(a, b)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([-1.,  1.])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Check that the solution is correct:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.allclose(we.dot(a, x), b)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
